  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="1c49-5cd8-a327-e916" name="Mike Target" hidden="false">
      <description>When a Spotting Team successfully Ranges In an Artillery Unit with Mike Target, they may immediately roll to Range In another Artillery Unit. If successful, the second Artillery Unit is treated as Ranging In on the same attempt as the first.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="a59f-ee99-cc7f-9fdf" name="Brutal" hidden="false">
      <description>A single direct hit from one of the 105mm high-explosive shells is generally enough to annihilate an unprotected target. Infantry and guns hit in Direct Fire must re-roll their saves.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="9207-2761-d8bd-0b87" name="Night Attack" hidden="false">
      <description>If a Force with Night Attack is the attacker in a mission where the defender has Minefields, the player may attack at night. If they do so, Night Fighting rules (see page 113 of the rulebook) are in effect at the start of the game.
British Units from Formations with Night Attack can move freely from the start of the game. Friendly Units from other Formations or Support may not move out of their Deployment Area until morning breaks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="000d-ab93-9f25-134d" name="Mind &amp; Heart" hidden="false">
      <description>Teams from this Unit that start their Movement Step adjacent to a cliff or mountainside (or another similar Impassable terrain feature) roll a Skill Test; if successful, the Team may move using Terrain Dash across the terrain.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
